This sentence from the containment procedures:



Civilians entering these programs are to have their backgrounds checked for previous forklift certification that was previously revoked.
附加记录：    

Seems to be in conflict with this one from the description:



In addition, all evidence that the target was ever forklift certified will be voided in some way during this event.
附加记录：    

Surely the background check won't find anything if all the evidence is gone? Unless I'm misunderstanding what's meant by  here.

Also, I don't get the flawed teaching. If people fail their test then their certification is revoked, they have good reason to believe it actually happened, and soon enough you've got headlines like . If people pass then they can easily shrug the whole thing off as a dream.

That stuff aside, I really love the concept of the Health and Safety Aliens taking over through Improved Forklift Operation.







